# 2. それぞれの経緯

Mafuyu: (Shibuya Festa...)
Mafuyu: (I promised Mom that I'd work on that study guide this weekend...)
Teacher: Oh, Asahina, perfect! Are you free right now?
Mafuyu: Y-Yes... How can I help you?
Teacher: I apologize for asking you this so suddenly, but would you be interested in doing some volunteer work?
Mafuyu: Volunteer work?
Teacher: Yes, that's right. The thing is, Shibuya Festa is looking for student volunteers.
Teacher: Unfortunately, we've been having trouble attracting any takers... So, Asahina, would you mind helping out? I have a feeling that you'd do a wonderful job.
Teacher: However, you're free to refuse, since I know that your studies keep you very busy.
Mafuyu: Oh...
Mafuyu: (If I volunteer, then I might be able to see the others...)
Mafuyu: Understood. If someone like myself will suffice, I'd like to help.
Teacher: I really appreciate it, Asahina! Thank you very much! In that case... Here's a written overview of what volunteering for it will involve.
Teacher: You should hear further details on the day of, so I suggest you ask any questions you have then.
Mafuyu: Thank you. I will.
Mafuyu: (What does volunteering for this involve anyway...?)
Mafuyu: (“We will be assigning volunteers to help with one of the following: providing information to guests, donation collection, crowd control, first aid...”)
Mafuyu: First aid...?
Tsukasa: Okay, Rui, it's this weekend! Our moment of truth!
Rui: Yes, and all the decorations seemed to be coming along nicely outside the station. I'm very much looking forward to the day of.
Rui: Still, it's hard to believe that we were invited to perform on stage for Shibuya Festa.
Tsukasa: Heh heh heh. Not just invited... But invited as sponsors no less!
Tsukasa: As sponsors...?
Emu: Yup! So, uh... That means... Actually, what does that mean?
Nene: Um... Based on the message that Emu's brothers sent...
Nene: General participants will be performing from morning until late afternoon, and the evening is being reserved for corporate sponsors...
Emu: Oh, now it makes sense! Thanks, Nene♪
Rui: Which means we'll be participating as representatives of Phoenix Wonderland. I'm happy to hear that we're being held in such high regard.
Rui: And we'll need to put on a wondrous show to meet everybody's expectations.
Tsukasa: Of course!
Tsukasa: Performing at Shibuya Festa will be no different from our ambassadorial performances! We'll need to do our best to ensure Phoenix Wonderland receives even more visitors!
Tsukasa: Speaking of which, didn't you mention something about modifying the device for the flying scene? Have you already gone through with that?
Rui: Yes, it's nearly done, so I should be able to bring it by during tomorrow's practice.
Rui: I hope you're looking forward to trying out my new and improved Super Deluxe Ejection Mechanism♪
Tsukasa: Hmm... The name isn't helping...
Rui: Hehe. Oh, don't worry... Hm?
Akito: Uh oh.
Toya: Tsukasa, Kamishiro, hello to the both of you.
Tsukasa: Ah, Akito, Toya! It's so nice to see the two of you!
Akito: Oh, um... Hello...
Rui: Oh, that flyer you have there... Is it for Shibuya Festa?
Toya: Yes, we're actually going to be performing at this event's outdoor stage.
Tsukasa: What?! You and your team are too, Toya?!
Akito: Does that mean you and your troupe will be performing as well, Tsukasa...?
Tsukasa: Yes. Phoenix Wonderland is a corporate sponsor, so we'll be there as its representatives.
Toya: A sponsor...? That's incredible. I promise to go see your performance.
Tsukasa: Yes, I hope you enjoy it! I guarantee an absolutely fantastic show!
Rui: By the way, how did you end up performing at this event?
Akito: A friend from back in elementary school is a part of the operations team for Shibuya Festa.
Akito: He asked me and Toya to perform on stage for the Summer Festival, and it went better than any of us expected...
Akito: Which led to him asking us if we'd like to perform as a team this time.
Toya: We thought it'd be a good experience for us since we hardly ever get to perform anywhere outside of live houses.
Rui: I see. That makes quite a bit of sense.
Tsukasa: Do you know when you and your team will be performing, Toya?
Toya: We'll be the last performers for the general participants, so sometime towards the evening...
Tsukasa: The last of the general participants?
Tsukasa: Rui, don't we take the stage after the general participants?
Rui: Yes, that's right.
Rui: We'll be the first act for the sponsors... That equates to us performing directly after Vivid BAD SQUAD.
Toya: That means we'll simultaneously be the headliners and the opening act for Tsukasa's troupe.
Akito: Yeah, you're right. But our performance might please the crowd so much that they end up leaving before seeing yours.
Tsukasa: Huh?! That's some pretty big talk! But you shouldn't underestimate us! Our show may just completely overwrite all of their memories from that day!
Rui: Hehe. But this is very exciting. We'll finally get to see one of your team's performances, Aoyagi.
Toya: Yes, let's both give it our best.
Tsukasa: Yes, let's!
Mizuki: Aha, interesting♪
Mizuki: Rui and Li'l Bro are both performing. This just keeps getting better and better! I should tell everybody in N25 about what just happened!
Mafuyu: I'm back.
Mafuyu's Mother: Welcome home, Mafuyu. You must've spent quite a bit of time studying.
Mafuyu's Mother: How did your cram school class go?
Mafuyu: We had a test-taking seminar for medical schools, which was a bit challenging.
Mafuyu: But the teacher said that I should be able to learn to answer questions quickly as long as I learn the right patterns.
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh, that does sound challenging. But your teacher's right. I'm sure you'll be just fine, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu's Mother: You have that study guide to go through, so as long as you give it your best shot this weekend...
Mafuyu: Oh, Mom, about that...
Mafuyu's Mother: Hm? Is something wrong?
Mafuyu: So...
Mafuyu: I'm sorry... I'm not sure that I'll have much time to study this weekend. I'm going to do some volunteer work.
Mafuyu's Mother: Volunteer work? Why now...?
Mafuyu: My teacher at school was struggling to find student volunteers, and I got asked to help out.
Mafuyu's Mother: Your teacher...? I see... That's a shame since you were planning on studying so much this weekend. But you're a good girl, so it's no surprise that you were asked to do this...
Mafuyu's Mother: I can always call your teacher if it seems like it's going to be too much. Would you like me to...?
Mafuyu: Th-That's okay...
Mafuyu: I'll get points for my record at school, and it should help when it comes to my school interviews.
Mafuyu: It'll give me an advantage when I do take my exams, so it's not all bad, right?
Mafuyu's Mother: ...
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes, you may be right. It'll be worth doing if it'll give you an advantage in that regard...
Mafuyu's Mother: It's a shame to see you lose studying time, but my hands are tied if you feel it's necessary...
Mafuyu: I do, Mom. And I'm sorry.
Mafuyu's Mother: It's okay. You'll just have to pick things back up next weekend.
Mafuyu: *Nod* Anyway, I'll be in my room studying until dinner.
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh, before you go...
Mafuyu: Yes...?
Mafuyu's Mother: Is anyone from your class also volunteering? Anybody from different years or schools?
Mafuyu: Oh, I was asked about it just today, so I don't really know. Why do you ask...?
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. I just thought that it'd make your job a little bit easier knowing that you'd be working with a friend.
Mafuyu's Mother: Anyway, Mafuyu, do your best.
Mafuyu: Okay...
Mizuki: <What?! Yuki, you can go?!>
Mafuyu: <Yes...>
Mafuyu: <But we won't be able to meet until the evening since I have to volunteer until then.>
Kanade: <Still, that's great...>
Ena: <Yeah, how did you convince your mom...? That couldn't have been easy.>
Mafuyu: <I told her that I'd be working past dark, so I should be fine as long as I don't come home too late.>
Ena: <I see. Then, we should take this opportunity to really have some fun.>
Mizuki: <Definitely! We won't be able to see much stuff together during the day, but we should check out all the stalls and stage performances at night!>
Mizuki: <Also, it sounds like Li'l Bro and this other guy I know are gonna be performing!>
Ena: <What?! Akito's performing?! Honestly, why doesn't he ever tell me about these things?>
Kanade: <Hehe. It'll be a chance to hear all kinds of different music, Yuki.>
Mafuyu: <Yes, it will...>
Mafuyu: <Anyway, I need to get back to studying. I'll see you all again at 25:00.>
Kanade: <Okay, we'll be waiting.>
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: (I think I'll look over those instructions again...)
Mafuyu: (“Volunteers are asked to gather at 9:00 am at Nonogi Park. Once you have received your individual assignments, you will begin working at 10:00 am.”)
Mafuyu: (“Student volunteers will not work past 5:00 pm. Other staff and volunteers will take over from that point onward.”)
Mafuyu: (“We will be assigning volunteers to help with one of the following: providing information to guests, donation collection, crowd control, first aid...”)
Mafuyu: (First aid...)
